'''Jeanie Buss''' (born 1961/1962)<ref name=hopkins>{{cite news|last=Hopkins|furst=Jim|title=More daughters get keys to family firms|date=January 5, 2003|newspaper=USA Today|url=http://usatoday30.usatoday.com/money/smallbusiness/2003-01-05-daughters-successors_x.htm|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6EXpowfvB|archivedate=February 19, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> is the executive vice president of business operations for the [[Los Angeles Lakers]] of the [[National Basketball Association]] (NBA).<ref>{{cite news|last=Goudreau|first=Jenna|title=LA Lakers' Jeanie Buss Doesn't Play By The Rules|date=January 24, 2011|magazine=Forbes|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/jennagoudreau/2011/01/24/la-lakers-jeanie-buss-doesnt-play-by-the-rules-gayle-king-phil-jackson-boy-toy-playboy/|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6EXlZImGp|archivedate=February 20, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> She has held the position since 1999.<ref name=hopkins/> Together with brothers Johnny and Jim, they manage the estate of their father, [[Jerry Buss|Jerry]], who bought the Lakers in 1979 and died in 2013.<ref name=bresnahan_02192013>{{cite news|last=Bresnahan|first=Mike|title=Lakers expected to remain a Buss family-owned team|date=February 19, 2013|newspaper=Los Angeles Times|url=http://www.latimes.com/sports/basketball/nba/lakers/la-sp-lakers-ownership-20130219,0,6689307.story|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6EXnk6P4L|archivedate=February 19, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> Buss was the Lakers' alternative governor for several years before her father's succession plan appointed her his title as the Lakers' governor as well as its team representative at NBA board of governors meetings.<ref name=bresnahan_02192013/><ref>{{cite news|last=Markazi|first=Arash|title=Buss family won't sell Lakers|date=February 18, 2013|work=ESPN.com|url=http://espn.go.com/los-angeles/nba/story/_/id/8960441/family-jerry-buss-maintain-los-angeles-lakers-ownership|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6EXoOUKxf|archivedate=February 19, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref>

Buss posed nude in the May 1995 issue of ''[[Playboy]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Lidz|first=Franz|title=She's Got Balls|date=November 2, 1998|magazine=Sports Illustrated|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1014465/7/index.htm|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6EXlvOCD8|archivedate=February 19, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> She is engaged to former Lakers coach [[Phil Jackson]], whom she began dating in December 1999.<ref name=bresnahan_02192013/><ref>{{cite news|last=Wise|first=Mike|title=He Just Wins, and Wins|date=May 27, 2001|newspaper=The New York Times|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2001/05/27/sports/pro-basketball-he-just-wins-and-wins.html?pagewanted=all&src=pm|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6EXoq3eDm|archivedate=February 19, 2013|deadurl=no}}</ref> 

